I suggest to use regex pattern matching instead - it will be more compact and readable, i.e.:
std::regex pattern{R"([_[:alnum:]]+)"};
bool ret = std::regex_match(tested_string, pattern);

It could work here, but I think that this would not improve code readability. What if we have multiple unused elements? Then we can't name everything '_'.

